Superbia's mindscape was a huge temple, with a lot of pillars and stairs. On top of it was a giant throne with gems in it.
All around were trees.
Morise blinks. "This looks... wonderful. It suits you." They're slightly glad to have their own body back, but... they maybe miss being with Superbia.
((wait is Superbia in her mindscape rn ?- ~~sorry i'm confused~~))
((Yee probably))
Superbia jumped from the stairs and rushed to Morise "Thank you ! I do love it too ! ~" She smiled
Morise immediately wraps their arms around Superbia. "Better." They say. "Much better."
She giggled and hugged them tightly "Aww, you missed me that much already ?"
"Hush, you." Morise rests their head on top of Superbia's. "But yes. I did miss you." They add.
She purred "You're *adorable* I missed you two Dearest"
//simp
Morise smiles. "So. We are... a single body right now. That is not something I expected to happen."
She nodded "Indeed, I wonder what caused this..." She shrugged "But it's not so bad"
"Indeed. I wonder... if we were calmer about it, would our minds... fuse as well?" Morise hums quietly. "I don't think its permanent, but still."
"Mmmm... Maybe, I feel like everything's possible at this point" She yawned "I wish I could've at *least* got time to take a breakfast before this"
"That would have been nice." Morise agrees. "Maybe if we eat breakfast together, we won't be hungry when we unfuse?"
Superbia nodded "Oh, smart ! I like it. We should try"
"I see..." Morise purses their lips. "You think we should just... let our minds relax and see what becomes of it? Only with your permission, of course."
"Of course ! ~ I don't see what else we could do anyway"
"Alright." Morise sits down, and closes their eyes. "I'll see you when we unfuse."
She sighed "Alright, I'll miss you my love !"
Morise is bouncing around excitedly. "We're fusing with *another fusion*, Superbia! Isn't this *interesting*?" They take her hand, making a purring noise.
She purred and hugged them "It is !! I'm quite excited !"
"It's *fascinating*." They say, pleased.
"It is indeed" She hummed "I wonder what we'll look like ~"
"As gorgeous as you do." They say, smiling.
She blushed and giggled "Aw, you ~" She gently boop their nose
They purr louder. "Only telling the truth."
She kissed their cheek "I know I am beautiful, but hearing from you always make my heart *melt*~" She was purring as well
They rest their chin on the top of her head. "Glad to hear it, because I like saying it."
"That's great then, My Dearest ! ~"
"Heh." They wrap their arms around her, purring.
She wrap her arms around them "Being Suprise is great~ Because I get to be one with you"
"I like it." They pull her closer. "We're wonderful together."
She nodded "We are ! ~ and it's a lot of fun !"
"It is." They grin. "Do you think Illuvies and Somnus would end up here, too? I mean, they'd have to. You're the only one with a mindscape."
She looked up, thinking for a moment "I guess, it would make sense !"
"It's new to me. Who knows?" They shrug.
"It's new to me too ! I guess we'll wait and see~"
The mindscape warps as Somnus appears, space bending and rippling around her. She swivels her head around, scoping things out.
Morise leaps back, taking Superbia into their arms. "Prediction correct." They say, after they've calmed down.
Illuvies was already there, stretching out and happily humming. “So *this* is was being in a mindscape is like! It feels so *open* and free!”
"You see why I like them?"
Superbia waved "Greetings, Greetings my Darlings ! Welcome to my Humble Temple !" She gestured at the giant temple, with the thrown on top
“Ahaha~! Fantastic, fantastic~!” he claps his hands together, overjoyed. “Fitting of a queen!”
She chuckled "Oh you ! ~ Although I rarely expect as many guests, so it might be slightly dusty"
Morise coughs and puts Superbia down. "I should come over here more often, then."
Superbia kind of just... Jumped to Somnus "Say, you're Illuvies friend, aren't you ?"

She nods.
"Yeees, we are friends."
She smiled and extended a hand "I am Superbia, a pleasure to meet you, Darling ! ~"
((somnus: *oh god another illuvies*
"Lovely to meet you, Superbia."

"You look like a fun one to hang out with ! Don't you think Dearest ?~" She turned her head to Morise
"I am *very* fun to hang out with."
"...." Morise, who sword-fought Somnus as soon as they met her, refrains from commenting.
Illuvies barks out a laugh, *very* amused by the situation. “Morise, dear, lighten up~! Superbia *loves* her, why don’t you?” he asks with a pout.

She nods sagely.
"I'm extremely cool, and also sexy."
"She's growing toxic mold in my vents." Morise raises an eyebrow.
"Oooo ! Mold you say ? Sounds quite intresting !" She clapped happily

"It *is* interesting. There's so much biodiversity in your air ducts now."
Environmentalist queen 💖
"Do we... *need* the biodiversity in my air ducts?"
"...Yes? What, do you not care about the environment, Morise?"
She put a finger to her chin "I've never thought too much about the environnement, Frankly..."
"I mean. Are you absolutely sure it's required?"

She clicks her tongue against the roof of her mouth.
"You're *exactly* what's wrong with society, Morise. This is why we need to do away with the ruling class."
Illuvies, although paying attention to the conversation, is strangely quiet.

Somnus Looks At Him.
"What's wrong, friend?"
"Illuvies dear, you've been awfully quiet"
“Nothing, my dears~ Simply enjoying the passing of the story,” he coos, cheek in his hand.
"The ruling class- We keep things in order, that's why we have them."
"Ruling sounds fun, but I prefer being *worshipped*" She hummed

She sticks out her tongue at him.
"You're so passive, Illuvies. You're as much a character as any of us in this story."
“Oh I’m *plenty* aware of that. I did not say it was *my* story that was passing~”
"Then what are you referring to?"
“I believe I’ve said enough.”
Superbia sighed and rolled her eyes "Come ooon Illuvies, tell us ! ~"
Morise folds their arm and shapeshifts another pair to put on their hips. Their shapeshifting is back, in this mindscape.
He says nothing, simply standing there and smiling at them— As if he knows something they don’t.
"I'll figure it out later." They wave their left arms dismissively. *He isn't getting me like that.*
He giggles, two fingers over his lips. *You truly are a simpleminded being, Morise.*
They immediately darken. "Simple*minded*? I was going off your previous attempts to goad and annoy me. It's only logical to assume you were trying to make me worry."

"...Keep your secrets, then."
If she really wants to know, she can *persuade* Illuvies into telling her later.
Superbia pouted "There will be no fights in *my* mindscape ! Morise, Dearest, please calm down..."
He holds his hands up defensively. “Don’t mind me, darling, only thinking!”
They sigh and wrap all four of their arms around Superbia, resting their head on hers.

She keeps her eyes fixed on Illuvies for a moment longer, then turns toward Superbia.
"I think we should celebrate this... Michael thing. Have a little party."

She clapped her hands "But of course !"
As her hand was rising, a big table with tea, cookies and other sweets appeared, along side Very Fancy Chairs
Somnus grins and climbs into one of the chairs, perching there with her legs crossed.
Morise hums appreciatively. "The chair designs are lovely." They murmur.
“So *quaint,*” he comments, very incorrectly sitting down in a chair.
(Somnus and Illuvies are both in the sits in chairs wrong gang)
Superbia giggled as she sat on the throne-like chair "Thank you Blueberry ! ~" She whispered to Morise
((Morise sits perfectly in chairs oh god))
They sigh at the nickname, and sit daintily on a chair. Their posture is perfect, unlike some others they could mention. They remember how to sit on a chair properly.
Somnus sees their impeccable posture and responds by slouching lower in the seat.
“Aww, *come on,* Morise! Where’s your sense of *adventure?* You simply *cannot* stay prim and proper ALL the time!” he coos, leaning over and placing his elbows on the table, chin in his hands.
Morise looks vaguely horrified.
Superbia ended up laying across her chair "We can all be more casual, we're fused afterall, aren't we ?"
"You're all terrible." They grumble, but curl up on the chair more comfortably, hooking their legs over the armrests.

"We're friends,"
She coos, shifting herself so that she's draped over the arms sideways.
"Best friends. We can be casual."

"*She* is my lover." Morise points at Superbia. "*You* are weird." They point at Somnus. "*He* is annoying." They finish by pointing at Illuvies. "This does not mean you two are my best friends. Superbia has that role, I think."
“I see, I see.. you truly are a lonely being,” he coos, grinning smugly at them as he gets comfortable in his seat.
"Aww, Morise, aren't the friends of your friends also your friends ?" She is attempting the Puppy Eyes™ technique

"I think we're *very* close friends."
She reaches over and takes a cookie, nibbling at it.
"We're inside eachother, aren't we?"
"........I can't say no to that face." They grumble at Superbia. "Honorary friends." They correct Somnus.
“...” Illuvies is quiet again, simply grinning mischievously at Morise.
Superbia happily smiled "Good ! I'd be so *sad* if my Dearest wasn't getting along with my friends..." She took a cup of tea and drank a bit
"You're such a peacemaker." Morise ignores Illuvies.
She grinned "The pros of being a goddess amongs human back on earth~" She hummed
"Still a goddess to me." They murmur.
She smirked "What was it Dearest ? I don't think I caught that~"

“...”
Illuvies turns to Somnus, Looking At Her. “It seems my dearest friend has realized.”
"You're still a goddess to me." They repeat, louder.

She looked smug and content "You're the most beautiful goddess to *me* Dearest ! ~"
She turns to Illuvies "... what is it ?..."
He continues to stay quiet, simply closing his eyes, placing his cheek in his hand, and humming delightedly.
"You know what I said about him being annoying earlier? This is why."
Somnus Blinks Knowingly at him, nibbling at her cookie.
Superbia took another sip, suspicious but too happy and thrilled by her tea party to notice anything

"What kind of cookies are these, Superbia?"
She bites back a laugh.
"They're good."
“I suppose *that* arc is over,” he sighs out, stretching his arms behind his head.
"*Arc*?" They look skeptically at Illuvies.

"Very basic and classic chocolate chips cookies~" She hummed
"Illuvies dear, what wonderful things are you seeing ?"
“My lips are sealed and my eyes are shut, my knight, I shall not spill a word.”
"Aww, come *ooooon* dear, this is no *fun*"
"Dramatic ass." They flick a hand dismissively at him.
“Mayhaps you’d like to take a look?” he asks, sipping his tea.
Superbia grinned "With pleasure ! ~"
"I don't feel like unfusing from Suprise. Unless Superbia wants to."
She shrugged "I honestly don't mind staying as Suprise for a bit"
"I like them. We're *together.*" They explain.
She nodded, humming "I *love* them too ! ~"
Somnus bounces her leg a little, excited.
"Fusing is so strange yet it feels so good... Especially with you, Dearest ! ~" She ate a cookie
"Exactly." They grin at her.
"I'm surprised," he pipes up suddenly, side-eying Somnus. "You truly care for the boy, don't you?"

She shrugs.
"I might."
"Who are you two talking about ?"

"Don't worry about it."
She grins in a Suspicious Manner.
"..." She looked at the two suspicious "There's too many secrets here... *I don't like it*"
Morise silently raises an eyebrow at the two. *Keep secrets from me if you will, but I will not have Superbia feel uncomfortable because of you two's bullshittery.*
"Don't worry, my loves! We are simply causing problem on purpose!"
She nods.
She slowly sips her tea "I don't like not being aware of something *fun* like this"
"It's a surprise, Superbia! You have to wait for it."
She pouted before letting out a sigh "***fiiiiiine*** but I still hate being left out of things like this"

"You'll find out eventually,"
She stifles a laugh, reaching for another cookie and scanning the other guests' faces for their reactions.
Illuvies cackles wildly, unafraid of how strange it may seem as he takes his own cookie. trying one out with a pleased hum.
Morise raises an eyebrow. "When are we going to unfuse, by the way?" They don't say it, but they want to know exactly what's going on here.
"Are you not having fun? *I* am having fun."
"I mean, sure. But I have work to do, and I can't spend all day fusing." They have to relearn to shapeshift, enter some data in, check the mun profiles, and then there's the rest of their jobs...
"We may unfuse if you truly desire so, though I am having a *blast.*"

"We're vibing!"
She gestures at the table for emphasis.
"We can do friend things in here, paint each others nails and shit. I haven't really done any classic friend things with anyone in... a few centuries now, at least."
"Do either of you have *anything* that even resembles a schedule?" They roll their eyes.
"I simply follow the story!"
"Why would I need a schedule?"

They raise their scorpion-pointed tail at them, blinking an eye onto it to glare at them while their face is in their hands.

"...Real shit?"

"...Yeees."

"You didn't did you- I have to get you back to the Plasma Kingdom, the Eternals need to know about this. Normally I'd have Barselius take you on his return, but that's no longer an option." They're speaking fast.
"Seems like *someones* a tad paranoid, don't you think, my friend?"

"Oh, absolutely."
She clicks her tongue on the roof of her mouth.
"So high strung- do you think they're in the right shape for doing their job in this state?"
Superbia was quietly sipping her tea
"Obviously, I am. I'm following protocol. I have no doubt the Eternals chose the right person to be their assistant."
"Nobody told *me* the protocol. I think this is very unfair of you."
"Because you weren't in the training program, I believe. It's not my fault the teacher plasma either abandoned you as a hopeless cause or didn't notice you at all."
"...Training for... what?"

They sigh. "When a Plasma is created, they are placed into a training program. They are taught many skills over the millennia, because we are very skilled. At the end of the training program, your rank determines your job. Ranks 5, 4, and 3 stay at the Plasma Zone as technological creators, historykeepers, etc. Rank 2s get to live among muns at the outposts to study them. They normally end up turning soft, it's a waste, really." They scoff. "Rank 1s, like me, are the best of the best, and are sent out to rule over the outposts or stay behind as secretaries to the Eternals." They say slowly, exaggerating each word by repeating it in sign language as they do so.
